                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1ra" to="102rb">1ra-102rb</locus>
                     <title type="Complete.">I. Dǝrsanä Mikaʾel “Homiliary for the Monthly Feasts of St. Michael”</title>
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipit and heading of the texts; names of the donors.</rubric>
                     <incipit>Fol. 1r, l. 1: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩ዱ፡ አምላክ፡ ንቀድም፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ጺሒፈ፡ ዜና፡ ዕበዩ፡ ወክብሩ፡ ወልዕልሁ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ሊቀ፡ መላእክት፡ ይስአል፡ ለነ፡ እምኀበ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላኩ፡ መሐሪ፡ ምሕረት፡ ወሣህል።<foreign xml:lang="en">[Fol. 1r, line 1] In the name of the Father, and the Son, and the Holy Spirit, one God. We start with the help of God the High, to write the story of the great, the honoured and the high saint Mikaʾel, the head of the angels…</foreign>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>Fol. 102rb, l. 24: ተፈጸመ፡ ድርሳነ፡ ሚካኤል፡ [fol. 102va] በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወበጸሎተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመነ፡ በዳህና፡ ወበሰላም፡ አሜን።<foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 102rb, l. 24] The Dǝrsanä Mikaʾel is done, by the peace of God and the prayer of Mikaʾel, and glory to God who makes possible to accomplish it well and in peace, amen.</foreign>
                     </explicit>
